00108 typedef struct Squeue
00109 {
00110     char                name[40];       /* Name of queue */
00111     int                 size;           /* Number of sinfo in queue */
00112     struct Sq_entry     *head;          /* First entry in queue */
00113     struct Sq_entry     *tail;          /* Last entry in queue */
00114     struct Sq_entry     *current;       /* current entry in queue */
00115 } Squeue;
00116 
00117 typedef struct Sq_entry
00118 {
00119     Squeue              *queue;         /* The queue this entry is in */
00120     struct Sched_Info   *sinfo;         /* The sinfo this entry holds */
00121     struct Sq_entry     *next_entry;    /* next sinfo in queue */
00122     struct Sq_entry     *prev_entry;    /* prev sinfo in queue */
00123     struct Sq_entry     *next_queue;    /* next queue this sinfo is in */
00124     struct Sq_entry     *prev_queue;    /* prev queue this sinfo is in */
00125 } Sq_entry;

00195  * This structure contains information used for the scheduler.  It will
00196  * be placed in the extension field of each oper
00197  */
00198 typedef struct Sched_Info 
00199 {
00200     float               sort_key1;              /* queue sort key 1*/

00209     Dep_Info            *dep_info;              /* dependence info for oper */
00210     Mdes_Info           *mdes_info;             /* mdes info for oper */
00211     Sq_entry            *entry_list;            /* linked list of Sq_entries */
00212 
00213     /* Support for safe"r" restricted percolation and wbs */
00214     int                 spec_cond;              /* Condition under which instruction can
00215                                                    be speculated */
00216     int                 ctl_dep_level;          /* control dependence level */
00217 
00218     /* 
00219      * Information used to determine when an oper can be taken off 
00220      * of the not_ready queue.
00221      */
00222     int                 num_depend;             /* original num input deps */
00223     int                 *operand_ready_times;   
00224 
00225     /* Information used for dynamic register pressure heuristic */
00226     float               benefit;
00227     Regtypes            kill_set;
00228     Regtypes            def_set;
00229     int                 branch_kill_set_size;
00230     int                 *branch_kill_set;
00231 
00232     /* Information used for static scheduling heuristic */
00233     float               priority;
00234     double              weight;                 /* oper weight */
00235     float               instr_prob;             /* Probability that the instr.
00236                                                    will be executed. */
00237     float               taken_instr_prob;       /* Probability that the branch will
00238                                                    be taken */ 
00239     float               not_taken_instr_prob;   /* Probability that the branch will
00240                                                    not be taken */ 
00241     int                 index;                  /* Index used when computing 
00242                                                    static priorities */

00244 
00245     /* Additional information used for static scheduling heuristic */
00246     int                 etime;                  /* earliest time an operation
00247                                                    can be scheduled given
00248                                                    dependencies */
00249     int                 *ltimes;                /* latest times an operation
00250                                                    can be scheduled given
00251                                                    dependencies.  this is an
00252                                                    array with one entry per
00253                                                    exit */
00254 
00255     /* Information used to exactly specify an instr schedule */
00256     int                 scheduled;              /* whether oper is scheduled */
00257     int                 issue_time;             /* Cycle instr is issued*/
00258     int                 issue_slot;             /* Actual slot scheduled for */
00259 #if 0
00260 no longer needed now that relative latencies are used. BLD 6/95
00261     int                 completion_time;        /* Cycle instr is complete */
00262 #endif
00263     int                 *relative_latency;      /* BLD 6/95 */
00264                                                 /* latencies associated with
00265                                                    each dest operand.  -1 means
00266                                                    there is no corresponding
00267                                                    dest operand. */
00268     int                 ready_time;             /* Cycle instr is ready */
00269     int                 earliest_slot;          /* earliest slot if scheduled in
00270                                                    the same cycle as an input
00271                                                    dependent instruction. */

00273     /* Candiates for delay slot */
00274     struct Sched_Info   *delay_sinfo;
00275 
00276     /* Information to support compiler controlled speculative execution */
00277     int                 home_block;

00280                                                  * reordering is done
00281                                                  * correctly. */
00282     L_Oper              *prev_br;
00283     L_Oper              *post_br;
00284 
00285     /* Information used to support write-back suppression */
00286     L_Oper              *extend_lr_down;        /* instr to extend all src operand
00287                                                    live ranges down to */
00288     L_Oper              *check_op;              /* best case check op */
00289
